				\begin{document}$$ \overrightarrow{w_i{w}_j\ }\in\ E\left(\mathrm{C}\mathrm{A}\mathrm{G}\right)\leftrightarrow\ \overrightarrow{v_i{v}_j\ }\in\ E\left(\mathrm{H}\mathrm{M}\mathrm{M}\right)\kern0.5em \mathrm{and}\ {u}_i={u}_j $$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M6"><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>w</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:msub><mml:mi>w</mml:mi><mml:mi>j</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mspace width="0.25em"/></mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="true">→</mml:mo></mml:mover><mml:mo>∈</mml:mo><mml:mspace width="0.25em"/><mml:mi>E</mml:mi><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">C</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">A</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">G</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced><mml:mo>↔</mml:mo><mml:mspace width="0.25em"/><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>v</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:msub><mml:mi>v</mml:mi><mml:mi>j</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mspace width="0.25em"/></mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="true">→</mml:mo></mml:mover><mml:mo>∈</mml:mo><mml:mspace width="0.25em"/><mml:mi>E</mml:mi><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">H</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">M</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">M</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced><mml:mspace width="0.5em"/><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">and</mml:mi><mml:mspace width="0.25em"/><mml:msub><mml:mi>u</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>u</mml:mi><mml:mi>j</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="40168_2015_93_Article_IEq3.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> if <italic>v</italic><sub><italic>j</italic></sub> is a delete state.</p>
      <p>The weight of an edge <inline-formula id="IEq4"><alternatives><tex-math id="M7">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \overrightarrow{w_i{w}_j} $$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M8"><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>w</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:msub><mml:mi>w</mml:mi><mml:mi>j</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="true">→</mml:mo></mml:mover></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="40168_2015_93_Article_IEq4.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> in CAG is defined as the log of the product of the transition and emission probabilities taken from the HMM:</p>
      <p><inline-formula id="IEq7"><alternatives><tex-math id="M9">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \mathrm{weight}\left(\overrightarrow{w_i{w}_j}\right) $$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M10"><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">weight</mml:mi><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mrow><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>w</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:msub><mml:mi>w</mml:mi><mml:mi>j</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="true">→</mml:mo></mml:mover></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="40168_2015_93_Article_IEq7.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> = log [ℙ<sub>transition</sub>(<italic>v</italic><sub><italic>i</italic></sub>→<italic>v</italic><sub><italic>j</italic></sub>)] + log [ℙ<sub>emission</sub>(<italic>v</italic><sub><italic>j</italic></sub>)] if <italic>v</italic><sub><italic>j</italic></sub> is a match state, <inline-formula id="IEq5"><alternatives><tex-math id="M11">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
